History is the page that tracks versions — restore the '4.0.0 (in
development)' section removed in the previous cleanup.

Elsewhere, drop 'since tik4net X' / 'new in 4.0' style sentences and
defer to History instead:
- transport pages: 'New in tik4net 4.0 — first released as…' banners
  reduced to a status-only alpha note
- WinBox Native pages: merged the resulting duplicate alpha banners,
  removed the version tag from the page titles
- Connection types: same banner rewording
- Change-tracking: dropped the '4.x feature' banner and the 3.x
  round-trip comparison in the intro (the migration section stays —
  it is actionable upgrade guidance, not just history)
- Getting-started / Testing-high-level / Home: removed inline '4.0' /
  '4.x' version tags
- login-versions: 'unified in tik4net 3.5.0' now defers to History

RouterOS version requirements (6.43+, 7.1+, 7.18+) are functional
prerequisites and are kept everywhere.

