+## 4.0.0 (in development)
+
+### ⚠️ Breaking changes
+* **`Save` default mode changed to `OnlyChanges`** — `Save` now diffs against a local snapshot instead of performing a `LoadById` round-trip. Entities not loaded via `Load*` are sent in full. To restore 3.x behavior globally: `TikDefaults.SaveMode = TikSaveMode.FullUpdate;` See [Change tracking](Change-tracking).
+
+### New features
+* **[Change tracking](Change-tracking)** — automatic snapshot on all `Load*` calls; `Save` sends only changed fields; no-op saves skip the API call. New types: `TikChangeTracker`, `TikSnapshot`, `TikDefaults`, `TikSaveMode`. New extension: `connection.ChangeTracker()`.
+* **New transports behind the same `ITikConnection`** (all _alpha preview_ — see [Connection types & capabilities](Connection-types-and-capabilities)):
+  * [REST](REST-connection) (`Rest` / `RestSsl`, RouterOS 7.1+)
+  * [Telnet](Telnet-connection) (`Telnet`, TCP 23)
+  * [SSH](SSH-connection) (`Ssh`, TCP 22 — satellite package `tik4net.ssh`)
+  * [MAC-Telnet](MAC-Telnet-connection) (`MacTelnet`, Layer-2 UDP 20561)
+  * [WinBox CLI](WinBox-CLI-connection) (`WinboxCli`) and [over MAC](WinBox-CLI-MAC-connection) (`WinboxCliMac`)
+  * [WinBox Native M2](WinBox-Native-connection) (`WinboxNative`) and [over MAC](WinBox-Native-MAC-connection) (`WinboxNativeMac`)
+* **[Safe Mode](Safe-Mode)** — `SafeModeTake()` / `SafeModeRelease()` / `SafeModeUnroll()` with automatic rollback-on-disconnect, across API / CLI / WinBox transports.
+* **Capability model** — `TikConnectionCapability` flags + `Supports` / `Require`; unsupported features fail closed with `TikConnectionCapabilityNotSupportedException`.
+* **Raw command pass-through** — `connection.CreateRawCommand(raw)` sends a payload in the transport's own dialect. See [Command translation](Command-translation-on-non-API-transports#raw-command-pass-through-createrawcommand).
+* **WinBox Native addressing by GUI names** — opt-in `connection.UseGuiNames = true`.
+* **[MCP server](MCP-server)** — drive any command over any transport from an AI assistant.
+
+> ⚠️ The non-API transports are **alpha previews** and the whole 4.0.0 line is still in development —
+> behaviour and API may change before release.
+
+---
+
